# Add Tests — Critical Test Coverage

Test the 20% that prevents 80% of disasters. Time-boxed effort.

## Workflow Pipeline

```
Shipper ──► Reviewer ──► Full Stack Dev + DB Admin (parallel) ──► Shipper ──► Documentor ──► Shipper
Branch       Identify       Write Tests                           Run Tests    Update Docs    Commit+PR
             Critical Gaps
```

## Steps

| # | Task | Role | Blocked By |
|---|------|------|------------|
| 1 | Create branch `test/critical-coverage-<area>` from main | Shipper | — |
| 2 | Identify CRITICAL untested code paths | Reviewer | 1 |
| 3 | Write minimal tests for critical application paths | Full Stack Dev | 2 |
| 4 | Write minimal tests for critical data integrity paths (if needed) | DB Admin | 2 |
| 5 | Run full test suite including new tests | Shipper | 3, 4 |
| 6 | Update documentation for new test coverage | Documentor | 5 |
| 7 | Commit and create PR to main | Shipper | 5, 6 |

## What Counts as Critical

**Test these (could cause disasters):**
- Authentication and authorization flows
- Data loss or corruption paths
- Payment and money flows
- Production outage scenarios

**Skip these:**
- UI formatting and styling
- Nice-to-have features
- Edge cases that won't impact production
- Anything that can be quickly fixed if it breaks
